ilog.concert

Interface IloIntMap

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IloMap

    public interface IloIntMap
extends IloMap
    The interface IloIntMap maps a list of integer elements. This list is indexed by sets of integers, floats, strings or tuples.

        Throws:

      • getAt

        int getAt(IloMapIndexArray indices)
          throws IloException
        This method returns the value of the element. Example with a map of int: M[i in 1..5][j in 1..2] = j M.getAt( [1][2] ) will return M[1][2] that is 2. It is the same as using M.getSub(1).get(2)
        Throws:
        IloException
